            <h2>Establishment of the geodetic base</h2>
             <p>The geodetic base or geodetic grid is a set of permanently stabilized points on the Earth's surface with specific coordinates in the horizontal and vertical sense. The points, or the coordinates of the geodetic base, are expressed in relation to the unique coordinate system.</p>
             <p>It is customary for construction and geodetic works to be carried out on the construction site from the same geodetic base, so that there is no discrepancy between the values observed at the same points.</p>
             <p>When establishing the geodetic base, care is taken to ensure that the established points are stable and reliable during all phases of building construction, but also after the building is put into operation, so that future monitoring of the movement and deformation of the building can be carried out from these points.</p>
             <p>After the field part and the physical establishment of the network, the office part of the work and equalization of the network is approached. Today, the equalization of the network is done by means of advanced computer programs specialized for this type of work, with the constant supervision of a geodetic expert. The final result of the network equalization is the fixed positions of the points (horizontal and vertical position) and the accuracy rating (reliability and precision) of the network.</p>
             <p>Establishing the geodetic base is one of the most precise works of the geodetic profession, because the success of the project (construction of tunnels, bridges, dams, highways, railways, buildings, etc.) depends on the quality of the constructed network.</p>
             <p><b>Only a well-executed geodetic basis is a prerequisite for the successful execution of the project.</b></p>
