           <h2>Monitoring displacements and deformations</h2>
             <p>Every built object is subject to movement and deformation. Displacements and deformations occur as a result of external loads - forces (wind, temperature change, tectonic and seismic influences, static and dynamic loading of the building), changes in the mechanical properties of the material from which the object is built, etc.</p>
             <p>Displacement is defined as a spatial change in the position of a discrete point on an object or ground. Deformation is the distortion or cracking of an object or soil, which is mainly caused by unequal displacements of points. Uneven displacements cause deformations such as bows, bends, twists and warps.</p>
