                 <p>Geodetic supervision is the control of the correctness of the execution of the contractor's works, that is, the control of the compliance of the execution of the works with the project. Construction supervision is a legal obligation of the investor.</p>
                 <p>A supervising engineer is a natural person who, according to a special law, has the right to use the professional title authorized engineer and carries out expert construction supervision on behalf of the investor.</p>
                 <p>Professional construction supervision is carried out during the construction of all buildings and the execution of all works for which a building permit and/or use permit is issued.</p>
                 <p>Geodetic supervision is mainly carried out during the construction of roads, due to the complexity of the project and the spatial distribution of the construction of the object.</p>
                 <p>Before the very start of work on the construction site, the investor is obliged to hand over to the geodetic supervising engineer the project documentation, the marked out route of the object and the operational polygons from which the route or axes of the future object were marked out.</p>
